re being logged.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Addressing binding for inner classes**\\\\n\\\\nIt sounds like I'll need to ensure the call site has the \\\\\\\"metadata required\\\\\\\" message when the field exists, so the getDeclaredField can succeed. Our non-static inner class should have this$0, but I wonder if it hasn’t been reached yet.\\\\n\\\\nI might need to force the binding directly to the non-static inner class, as the public API requires an instance. Perhaps a custom BindConstructorProvider could help if the default isn’t active. Using direct binding like `binder.bind(\\\\\\\"inner\\\\\\\", Outer.Inner.class)` should invoke the default provider, which recognizes the presence of this$0.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_xmzDm5vnVMmuD6gxA66nuBAE|fc_0acdf4a2616307f4016a252d6444a481959477cedff9170798\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"../../source_context/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/main/extracted/org/springframework/boot/context/properties/bind/BindConstructorProvider.java\"}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"../../source_context/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.2/main/extracted/org/springframework/boot/context/properties/bind/BindConstructorProvider.java\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 21638, \"output\": 713, \"cacheRead\": 10752, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 33103, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780821330555, \"responseId\": \"resp_0acdf4a2616307f4016a252d544f4c819597a9bb3c5cad6c95\"}}\n../7685-93742acd/human-intervention-logs/org.springframework.boot:spring-boot:4.0.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T08-32-21-519682Z.log:2832:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Improving